I"><h3 id="on-the-way-hungary-slovenia">On the way: Hungary, Slovenia</h3>

<p><b>Balaton</b> catfish stew on pancake, goulash soup, venison at “Kistücsök”</p>

<!--more-->

<h3 id="padua">Padua</h3>
<p>One should go see the Scrovegni chapel 
but if time is short, the mint coffee and the zabaione at
<a href="https://www.caffepedrocchi.it/en/"> Caffe Pedrocchi </a> 
must be tried first.</p>

<h3 id="bologna">Bologna</h3>
<p>Of course tagliatele al ragu (what everyone else calls bolognese sauce).
But take your time to admire the 
<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/29/bologna-seals-off-leaning-tower-fears-tilting-too-far"> 
leaning towers </a> 
one of them, apparently, even more inclined than the famous Pisa one.</p>

